{
  "day": 62,
  "key": "day_62_crucifixion",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "Condemned Though Innocent"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "Though Pilate declared him innocent,",
      "Jesus was handed over to be crucified."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "innocent",
        "icon": "balance",
        "label": { "en": "No Basis for a Charge" },
        "lines": [
          "Pilate said,",
          "“I find no basis for a charge against him.”",
          "But the crowd shouted,",
          "“Crucify! Crucify!”",
          "Finally, Pilate handed him over",
          "to be crucified."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "cross",
        "icon": "close",
        "label": { "en": "They Crucified Him" },
        "lines": [
          "Carrying his own cross,",
          "Jesus went out to Golgotha,",
          "the place of the Skull.",
          "There they crucified him,",
          "and with him two others,",
          "one on each side,",
          "and Jesus in the middle.",
          "The soldiers divided his garments,",
          "fulfilling what had been written."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "mockery",
        "icon": "campaign",
        "label": { "en": "Mocked for Who He Claimed to Be" },
        "lines": [
          "Those who passed by mocked him:",
          "“If you are the Son of God,",
          "come down from the cross.”",
          "The leaders said,",
          "“He saved others,",
          "but he cannot save himself.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "faith",
        "icon": "favorite",
        "label": { "en": "Remember Me" },
        "lines": [
          "One of the criminals beside him said,",
          "“We are punished justly,",
          "but this man has done nothing wrong.”",
          "Then he said,",
          "“Jesus, remember me",
          "when you come into your kingdom.”",
          "Jesus answered,",
          "“Today you will be with me in paradise.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Why do you think Jesus was mocked for who he claimed to be? What does his promise of paradise to the criminal suggest about his authority—even while on the cross?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["John 19:1–24", "Matthew 27:39–44", "Luke 23:39–43"]
  }
}
